Key Match Events: The Phillies suffered a 9-1 loss to the Nationals on Friday night.
Ranger Suárez allowed six runs on seven hits and two walks in two innings.
Pre-Game Insights: The Phillies would like to have home-field advantage through the NLCS and World Series.
Ranger Suárez hoped to show positive signs in his final start of the regular season on Friday.
Zack Wheeler can make voters think harder about his NL Cy Young Award candidacy with a strong performance on Saturday evening against the Nationals.
Post-Match Reflections: Suárez said through the team’s interpreter, 'It didn’t happen. Let’s turn the page and just have a strong mind going into the playoffs now.'
Phillies manager Rob Thomson said, 'I always have confidence in him because I think he’s very poised, that slow heartbeat comes into play.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies own the season tiebreaker over the Dodgers, so if they finish tied, they would get home-field advantage.
Aaron Nola pitches Sunday. He needs only 5 2/3 innings to reach 200 innings.
Trea Turner needs one stolen base for 20, which would give him the fourth 20-20 season of his career.
Others: The Phillies clinched the NL East on Monday. They clinched a first-round bye in the postseason on Wednesday.
